  "instructions": [
    "Heat oil in a pan over medium heat.",
    "Add chopped onions and minced garlic to the pan, sautéing until fragrant and translucent.",
    "Stir in tarragon leaves if using fresh or dried, cook for about 1 minute.",
    "Gradually add chicken broth or water while stirring continuously to avoid sticking.",
    "Simmer for 5 minutes to allow flavors to meld together.",
    "Fold dumplings gently into the sauce as it simmers. Cook until heated through and dumplings are tender but not falling apart.",
    "Garnish with lettuce leaves before serving."
